            <pb n="2"/> The brig Virginia Planter, James Merrifield, <lb/>Master, arrived at
                    Liverpool, brings information <lb/>that on the 5th of May, General Wayne, with
                    <lb/>two thousand provincials, had attacked to<lb break="no"/>tally destroyed
                    most of the Indian towns at the <lb/>back of Georgia, for near two hundred miles
                        a<lb break="no"/>round the river. That M'Gilvray, and his ar<lb break="no"/>my of savages, after an unsuccessful and bloody <lb/>engagement, had fled to
                    the woods, where the <lb/>General left them, and returned to Savannah.â€“
                    <lb/>This expedition was undertaken about the begin<lb break="no"/>ning of
                    March, winch has been crowned with the <lb/>expected catastrophe, and though the
                    Cherokee, <lb/>Miami, and Chiquesaw tribes, may mediate re<lb break="no"/>venge
                    at some future period; it is not likely they <lb/>will be in a condition to
                    disturb the settlers for <lb/>some years to come.</p>
